<paragraph id="8BD4368F3C6A2E4842E5F938FB53B3ED" blockId="14.[151,1437,1757,2035]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,152,1907]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="B91FEA9D3C6A2E4942E5F938FF31B5E1" bold="true" box="[151,214,1757,1783]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Type.</emphasis>
Jacoby did not mention the number of specimens under study, but he reported his personal collection as the only type depository. At present, a single 
<typeStatus id="54D0882D3C6A2E49401FF8E4FD23B40D" box="[621,708,1793,1819]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">syntype</typeStatus>
is housed in the collection of BMNH. The type designation was made as follows, in order to stabilize the epithet. 
<typeStatus id="54D0882D3C6A2E4940BBF8C0FCD9B42B" box="[713,830,1829,1855]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
(by present designation): 
<specimenCount id="9D6DFD063C6A2E494615F8C0FB99B429" box="[1127,1150,1829,1855]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, glued, aedeagus and de- tached abdomen glued on the same card bearing the specimen // “Rep. Argent. Prov. B. Aires” [white label, handwritten] // “Jacoby Coll. 
<date id="FFD5104F3C6A2E4943DEF888FDE9B491" box="[428,526,1901,1927]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" value="1909" valueMax="1928">1909-28</date>
a.” [white label, printed] // “Cryptoceph. bivitticollis Type Jac.” [blue label, handwritten] // “Type H. T.” [rounded white and red label, printed] // “This is 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D0C3C6A2E4941B7F874FBD7B4BD" authorityName="Haldeman" authorityYear="1849" box="[965,1072,1937,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Griburius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Griburius</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D0C3C6A2E49464BF874FB5CB4BD" box="[1081,1211,1937,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Metallactus</taxonomicName>
not 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D0C3C6A2E49469FF874FEAAB4D9" authority="Chamorro 2010" authorityName="Chamorro" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cryptocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cryptocephalus Chamorro 2010</taxonomicName>
” [white label, handwritten] // “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D0C3C6A2E4940C1F850FB89B4D9" authority="(Jacoby, 1907)" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[691,1134,1973,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivitticollis">
<emphasis id="B91FEA9D3C6A2E4940C1F850FC37B4D9" box="[691,976,1973,1999]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Metallactus bivitticollis (</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B7E3C6A2E4941A2F850FB82B4D9" author="Jacoby, M." box="[976,1125,1973,1999]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" pagination="829 - 855" refId="ref37547" refString="Jacoby, M. (1907) Descriptions of new species of South-American beetles of the Cryptocephaline division of the Family Chrysomelidae. Proceedings of the General Meetings for Scientific Business of the Zoological Society of London, May-December, 1907, 829 - 855. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1907. tb 06961. x" type="journal article" year="1907">Jacoby, 1907</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<subScript id="17EF34CA3C6A2E494605F859FB13B4DB" attach="right" box="[1143,1268,1980,1997]" fontSize="7" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">
<typeStatus id="54D0882D3C6A2E494605F859FB13B4DB" box="[1143,1268,1980,1997]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">LECTOTYPUS</typeStatus>
</subScript>
D. Sassi des.” [red label, printed] // (
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE4A3C6A2E4943F9F83CFE02B4E5" box="[395,485,2009,2035]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">BMNH</collectionCode>
). A second potential 
<typeStatus id="54D0882D3C6A2E4940B8F83CFCC6B4E5" box="[714,801,2009,2035]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">syntype</typeStatus>
is housed in the Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales, 
<collectingRegion id="49AFF86D3C6B2E4842E5FF7CFEC9B3A5" box="[151,302,153,179]" country="Argentina" name="Ciudad Autonoma de Buenos Aires" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Buenos Aires</collectingRegion>
(Bachmann e Cabrera, 2010). It is labelled as follows: “Rep. 
<collectingCountry id="F37C761F3C6B2E4841ADFF7CFBA9B3A5" box="[991,1102,153,179]" name="Argentina" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Argentina</collectingCountry>
Prov. 
<collectingRegion id="49AFF86D3C6B2E4846E4FF7CFACAB3A5" box="[1174,1325,153,179]" country="Argentina" name="Ciudad Autonoma de Buenos Aires" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Buenos Aires</collectingRegion>
<date id="FFD5104F3C6B2E484741FF7DFA9CB3A5" box="[1331,1403,152,179]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" value="1895-01">I.1895</date>
C. Bruch” [printed, date handwritten] // “Cotypus” [pale green label, printed] // “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D0C3C6B2E484181FF58FAB8B3C1" authority="Jac." authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1907" box="[1011,1375,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cryptocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivitticollis">Cryptocephalus bivitticollis Jac.</taxonomicName>
” [red frame, handwritten by Bruch]. However, it was not possible to examine this second specimen.
</paragraph>
